Boil a half-full kettle.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%mins}. Drain in a #sieve{} and pop
back in the pan.

Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in another large saucepan on medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook until slightly browned, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

Once the mushrooms have browned, stir in the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g},
@Coconut Milk{180%ml}, @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer
things milder), @Thai Green Style Paste{45%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g},
@King Prawns{150%g} and @Sugar{½%tsp}.

Bring the curry to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is
cooked through, ~{10-12%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the curry's ready, squeeze in half the lime juice from the lime wedges.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @?Water{}
if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and share between your #serving bowls{}. Spoon
over your Thai green style chicken curry.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!